(2) “ Authorised person ” means—

(a) in paragraph 2, a person authorised for the purposes mentioned in sub-paragraph (1)(a)(a)");

(b) in paragraph 4, a person authorised for the purposes mentioned in sub-paragraph (1)(b)(b)");

(c) in other paragraphs of this Schedule, a person authorised for the purposes mentioned in sub-paragraph (1)(c)(c)").

(3) An authorisation under this paragraph must be in writing.

